      • add

        public void add(T t)
        Adds an element to the queue. If the queue contains maxSize elements, e will be compared to the lowest element in the queue using comparator. If e is greater than or equal to the lowest element, that element will be removed and e will be added instead. Otherwise, the queue will not be modified and e will not be added.
        Parameters:
        t - - Element to be added, must be non-null.

      • asList

        public List<T> asList()
        Returns:
        Returns a view of the queue as a Collections.unmodifiableList(java.util.List) unmodifiableList sorted in reverse order.
